nstitute Lexington  VA 24450 Security Awareness In accordance with state law  VMI requires anyone who uses its network to complete Security Awareness Training within thirty days of being granted access to the network  and then again once or twice annually after that   Normal training periods will be during the months September and January  Security awareness is an initiative designed to inform the user community about the importance of adequately securing their data  It teaches the users to be responsible for their own data  and it advises them on some best practices for securing their workstation from potential intruders  Currently VMI is using the SANS Securing the Human Virtual Learning Environment for its training   This is a hosted Learning Management System used by SANS to deliver its copyrighted security awareness training solution  Click here for directions and a link to the Security Awareness Training Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Help Desk Monday   Friday  7 00 am   4 00 pm  Self Service Portal P   540  464 7643 F   540  464 7222 Help vmi edu Email IT Webmaster Information Technology 315 Nichols Engineering Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450  Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Help Desk Monday   Friday  7 00 am   4 00 pm  Self Service Portal P   540  464 7643 F   540  464 7222 Help vmi edu Email IT Webmaster Information Technology 315 Nichols Engineering Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Information Technology Information Technology Information Security Informa